						<summary>

						<p>Stone pillar found near the old fort wall, now kept near the Ayurvedic dispensary.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1225, Makara Saṅkrānti</hi> corresponding to 1303 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to records the gift of land to god Gaṭṭi Mallīśvara Mahādēva at Gurṟālaguṇta. The name of the donor is lost.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
